   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Delivering Aid Directly To Japan&apos;s Tsunami Victims</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Japan&apos;s Tsunami victims are living in shelters or damaged neighborhoods without power or heat and running very short of basic necessities. SHINE HUMANITY arrived in Japan on March 18, and has been coordinating with partners and local officials in the port town of Ishinomaki ever since, providing logistical and operational support- delivering food, water, medicines and compassion to families living in shelters and helping to provide heating oil to citizens whose homes were spared but have no heat</narrative>
  </description>
